{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make Comprehensive Gynaecology Education Mandatory in Secondary Schools",
        "additional_details": "Current RSHE focuses mainly on reproduction, contraception & sexually transmitted infections. It does not adequately cover gynaecological conditions, menstrual disorders, pelvic pain, hormonal health beyond contraception, or how to recognise abnormal symptoms & seek medical help. Conditions such as endometriosis, adenomyosis, fibroids & PCOS affect a significant proportion of women & girls. Many report years of delayed diagnosis, often because they did not realise their symptoms were not normal.",
        "background": "Require all secondary schools in England to include comprehensive gynaecology and women\u2019s health education within the statutory RSHE curriculum.",
